    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound example of the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant, featuring VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. The drivetrain is anchored by a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle, delivering linear power to the rear wheels. Significant preventative maintenance has been completed, including the installation of a dual-row IMS bearing kit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS), ensuring the internal architecture's longevity. The chassis maintains its precision with a well-sorted multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts that communicate road texture without excessive NVH. Braking performance is handled by four-piston Brembo monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing consistent pedal feel and minimal fade. While the finish reflects its history as a driver's car, the mechanical vitals remain within factory tolerances, offering a pure, hydraulic-steering experience.",
